              "question": "How does stock quantity update automatically?",
              "answer": "Every stock IN, stock OUT, or adjustment transaction automatically updates the product's current quantity. When an order is marked as completed, stock is also auto-adjusted. No manual quantity editing is ever allowed — ensuring complete accuracy.",
              "defaultOpen": true
            },
            {
              "question": "Can multiple users login at the same time?",
              "answer": "Yes! Stoxen supports concurrent multi-user access. Each user has their own JWT-based session. Role-based access control ensures that each user only sees and does what their role permits."
            },
            {
              "question": "Is my warehouse data safe and private?",
              "answer": "Absolutely. All passwords are hashed with bcrypt. API access requires JWT authentication. Role-based permissions prevent unauthorized access. All actions are logged to an immutable activity log."
            },
            {
              "question": "How do I generate and download reports?",
              "answer": "Navigate to the Reports section, select a report type (Inventory, Transactions, Low Stock, Suppliers, or Orders), set your date range and filters, then click Download PDF or Download CSV."
